result.execSummary:
The defendant Channing E Sanders was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

2:43 pm  Court in session.  Case Called.  Appearances given.  
ADA Matthew R. Leusink appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deft Channing E Sanders in court with Atty Jason Sanders. 
Matter is before the Court for sentencing hearing in both files.  Court recites charges and maximum potential penalties.  Court has reviewed both files (2015CF000460 and 2016CF000030).  Court notes there is not a victim impact statement nor a restitution request on file.  The State has complied with victim notification.  Atty Sanders has reviewed the PSI with his client and has one minor corrections which he notes for record. Defendant is ready to proceed to sentencing.  
2:45 pm  Argument by Atty Leusink.  
2:56 pm  Argument by Atty Sanders.  Atty Sanders advises Court that deft is on probation for 2 years which commenced in Sept. of 2015.  Deft began attending NA meetings approximately a month or 2 ago.  
3:05 pm  Statement by Deft.  Response by Deft to Court's questions.  
3:07 pm  Court proceeds with making record and sentencing the Deft. 

On file 2015CF000460:  
2 yrs IC + 2 yrs ES for total sentence of 4 yrs prison;  
Eligible for CIP and SAP;  IMPOSED AND STAYED;  
4 years probation;  

On file 2016CF000030:
WITHHELD SENTENCE; 4 years probation

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION ON BOTH CASES:
1)  No contact with victims Walter Kraayvanger, Thomas Dye or America Pawn Store of Chicago, IL.  No contact with co-actors Edward Meyer, Tyler Debaets or Anthony Rodriguez.  
2)  No alcohol or illegal drug possession or use.  Any prescribed medication must be prescribed to and taken by the defendant as directed.  
3)  AODA assessment and follow through with all treatment recommendations.  A referral should be submitted within the first 30 days of supervision.  
4)  Counseling as directed by Agent.  
5)  Pay court costs.  Provide DNA sample and pay surcharge.  
6)  Obtain G.E.D. or H.S.E.D.  Maintain full-time school or employment or a combination of the two.  

Dead time credit to be confirmed with the jail by Atty Sanders. 
Court warns defendant that she is prohibited from possessing firearms and she may not vote until her civil rights are restored.   

3:25 pm  Court in recess.
